1) Write a python program to replace special symbol in string with # character.
import re

string = input("Enter a string: ")
# Replace special symbols with '#'
modified_string = re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z0-9 ]', '#', string)
print("Modified string:", modified_string)

2) Write a Python program to find the repeated items of a tuple and remove 
repeated items of a tuple and display updated tuple.

t = (1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 5, 1, 6, 3)
print("Original Tuple:", t)
repeated = set()
seen = set()
for item in t:
 if item in seen:
 repeated.add(item)
 else:
 seen.add(item)
print("Repeated items:", tuple(repeated))
updated_tuple = tuple(set(t))
print("Updated Tuple:", updated_tuple)

